⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Positional Encoding
node TTU1 · TTU1 · ⟦Positional Encoding:TTU1:83c1af⟧

WHO   — Positional Encoding — injecting order · sinusoid → RoPE
WHAT  — The fix for a real limitation: self-attention is permutation-invariant (it sees a bag of tokens), so position must be added — sinusoidal in the original, RoPE (rotary) in most modern models.
WHERE — TTU1 · Transformer Tech Universe  Framework inputs: Attention Is All You Need (Vaswani 2017); interpretability literature; David's deck encoding  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because without it the transformer literally cannot tell 'dog bites man' from 'man bites dog' — attention alone has no sense of order.
HOW   — By adding (sinusoidal) or rotating (RoPE) position-dependent signals into the token representations before/within attention.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Attention is order-blind on its own — I am the only reason the transformer knows that first is not last.

